vectorData.altText: Identify the class of epithelium B.
That's right!  The epithelial lining of the anus is composed of  keratinized stratified squamous epithelium.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

The transition zone between the rectum and the anus is called the pectineal line, PL. It marks the junction between the simple columnar epithelium of the colon, SCE, and the stratified squamous nonkeratinized epithelium of the anal canal, SSE. As shown clearly here, the SSE becomes keratinized, SSE(K) at the anus.
